Base:Description.spring: The meadow is dressed in her freshest attire. Her grassy dress sways with the wind while floral patterns of rich colors refresh the dewy green of her gown. Longing arms of the surrounding wood reach bouquets of their best selection toward her, tempting her to dance in reception. Little messengers pass secret words between the meadow and the woods, with only their attentive eyes, swift feet and lingering smiles hinting at the contents. Jealous birds swoop down and intercept vibrant lizards, catching them to feed their offspring. Busy insects and lazy snails observe the enfolding events.
Base:Description.summer: A sunlit and grassy meadow. The sky here is bright pale blue and entirely open; not a cloud or imperfection marks its body. Gold-tinted rays of orange and yellow beam down to constantly bathe the area in a warm, vibrant glow. Ripened berries on prospering trees and elaborate vines, along with a myriad of mature, colorful flowers litter the surroundings for as far as the eye can see. Insects of all sorts busily flit through the air creating a natural and rhythmic symphony of noise as they go about preparing for the upcoming fall and winter seasons.
Base:Description.autumn: A colorfully leaf-strewn meadow. Amongst the evergreens a few deciduous trees have begun to wilt and lose their leaves, the wind picking up those that have fallen to litter the grass of the clearing with star-patterned, rich hues of orange, red, yellow, and brown. The once-colorful flowers have dimmed in their vibrancy, with some even drooping or wilting in response to the decreasing temperature. Only the strongest grasses manage to remain standing tall and proud against the abuse of the whipping wind, chilly air, and increasing rain. Pools of water have begun to collect upon the topsoil, turning the formerly lush floor into a watery, slosh-worthy wonderland. The sky is overcast and dappled with dark clouds which splatter the area with releases of rain in irregular intervals.
Base:Description.winter: A frost-glazed meadow. The evergreen trees surrounding the clearing and the strong grasses on the meadow floor still bear a moderate amount of color despite the season, but all other vegetation clearly shows the effects of the continuously decreasing temperature. The once flowering plants have lost their vibrant blooms, while the majority of trees have had their leafy gowns stripped from their bodies, exposing them completely to the harsh, outdoor elements. The ground crunches audibly beneath the feet of those who travel through, but otherwise the area is eerily silent and void of the vivacious noises of life that occupied it only months ago. Small splotches of snow can be seen here and there, signs of the recent past's weather. Unsurprisingly, mother nature's handiwork has been preserved by freezing rains and the icy embrace of the winter air.

Base:Description.spring: A blossoming meadow stretches out before your eyes to melt into the fresh green mass of woods that caringly embraces the area in a treasuring fashion. The playful rays of the sun lend their bright golden shine to the freshly awakened vegetation.The moon's gentle light coats the sleepy vegetation with its silvery sheen.
Base:Description.summer: A sunlit and colorfully-decorated meadow littered with tall, proud trees, and vibrant, mature flowers fills the expanse of your gaze. The hot rays of the sun beam down encouragingly from the heavens, constantly bathing the area in bright, life-giving light.The silvery-white rays of the moon surround the area with a clear luminosity, lending a high sheen to the fully blossomed plants and casting impressive shadows from the lush, leafy trees.
Base:Description.autumn: A colorfully leaf-strewn meadow littered with freshly-tumbled vegetation in hues of orange, red, yellow, and brown. The freshly-fallen leaves coat the floor in a blanket of lush and colorful, rain-kissed stars.The yellowish light of the partially-concealed moon occasionally streaks down from the sky to create a play on shadows against the leaf-littered ground.
Base:Description.winter: A frost-glazed meadow adorned in the naked robe of winter. The overcast sky keeps the area dreary in appearance and assures the survival of the frost which clings to every open surface and body available.The barely noticeable moon keeps the surrounding area shrouded in a mask of darkness, rarely peeking out to cast a glint of light at the frost-tipped grasses which twinkle in response.

spring.day: Colorful patches of spring flowers contrast the fresh green of the grass dressing the meadow into a vivid, light-hearted spring gown. Snowdrops linger at the edge of the woods, while the deep purple of the shy violets hides in the grass. Haughty tulips and vain narcissus struggle for your attention proudly waring their colors. The trees small, bashful petals pale in their timid envy. Their scent however conquers the winds and travels through the meadow.
spring.night: The stars gently touch upon the sealed buds of the fresh flowers that seek shelter in the lush grass. The cool wind joins the nocturnal insects to whistle a soothing lullaby. Nosy ferns and quiet mushrooms sneak out of their cover to observe the creatures of the sun.

spring.night: The stars gently touch upon the sealed buds of the fresh flowers that seek shelter in the lush grass. The cool wind joins the nocturnal insects to whistle a soothing lullaby.

Base:Description.spring: Proliferous, dewy green grass spouts from the rich, dark earth. Colorful flowers dance with the spring breeze in this floral temple worshiping life.
Base:Description.summer: The lush green grass. The grass is tall and seems to have grown quite a lot, flowers frequently dot the area with a sunny brightness.
Base:Description.autumn: The brindled green grass. The grass is tall, overgrown and strewn with the falling leaves of the trees, every now and then is a streak of brown signifying the season.
Base:Description.winter: The frosted wilting grass. Having grown colder, the grass has wilted and only the strongest still stands.

Base:Description.spring: Proliferous, dewy green grass spouts from the rich, dark earth.

spring.day: Jovial insects hum and buzz an excited melody while paying their dutiful visit to the freshly spouted buds and blossoms of the meadow's spring flowers. Bees and wasp gossip over violets, chiding the early butterflies for their attire of last year's fashion. Naughty flies play their pranks with the sleepy ladybird.
spring.night: Quiet buzzing mingles with soft flapping of fluffy wings. Insects of the night sneak after their nightly business. Anxious moths chide energetic fireflies and shady butterflies dust their wings with the silver of the stars.

spring.day: Jovial insects hum and buzz excitedly while paying their dutiful visit to the freshly spouted buds and blossoms of the meadow's spring flowers.
spring.night: Quiet buzzing mingles with soft flapping of fluffy wings. Insects of the night sneak after their nightly business.

Base:Descriptions.Base:Description: gentle slope in the middle of the meadow
A single slope, that gently arches over the middle of the meadow breaks the flat surface of the clearing. The uneven bends of the ground intone the enlivened dynamics of the clearing.

Base:Descriptions.Base:Description: the patches of trees encircling the meadow

The meadow is encircled by the caring embrace of an assortment of trees, providing a firm contour to the clearing and a convenient hiding place for wild animals. Occasionally the walls of Triskellian can be spotted through the western section of the woods.
The meadow is encircled by the caring embrace of an assortment of trees.
White walls proudly reach toward the sky in the western horizon praising the glory of Triskellian. The trees surrounding the clearing awedly adorn the base of the walls.
The white walls of Triskellian decorate the western horizon over the trees that embrace the clearing.
